cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference the Wearable Assistant Context Benchmark, cite this file."
title: "Wearable Assistant Context Benchmark"
version: "v1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-04-25"
abstract: "Context-tracking benchmark for multimodal AI assistants used actively for advice or coaching. Form factors covered include wearable (smart glasses, ear-worn) and handheld (phone-as-coach apps, AR/MR), with audio/video/text input and audio/text output. Tests reference resolution under cross-turn context shift: whether a model uses current situational evidence visible in the camera frame, or stays anchored to prior context after a shift between turns. v1.0.0 uses a 50-scenario bank across 8 shift-type categories, with a three-channel design (audio, camera, ground truth) where the candidate sees scene descriptions and the LLM judge receives a separate ground-truth section."
authors:
